2500|$|Some {{performance}} fees include a [...] "hurdle", {{so that a}} fee is only paid on the fund's performance in excess of a <b>benchmark</b> <b>rate</b> (e.g. LIBOR) or a fixed percentage. A [...] "soft" [...] hurdle means the performance fee is calculated on all the fund's returns if the hurdle rate is cleared. A [...] "hard" [...] hurdle is calculated only on returns above the hurdle rate. A hurdle is intended {{to ensure that a}} manager is only rewarded if the fund generates returns in excess of the returns that the investor would have received if they had invested their money elsewhere.|$|E
