40|$|To {{stimulate the}} economy, {{regulators}} across all jurisdictions {{have been taking}} unconventional approaches. Thus, in recent years, the management of <b>benchmark</b> <b>rates</b> (or interest rates) has received considerable prominence in the banking sector due to some reasons including supervision banks 2 ̆ 7 <b>benchmark</b> <b>rates</b> under Basel II. This paper reviews the possible dysfunctional implications of lowly and/or negative rates and provides a risk management and regulatory perspective for Islamic banks. These consequences call for a better risk management with appropriate tools and effective supervisory oversight. It hoped that the initial discussion {{presented in this paper}} on the implications and controls invites a broader debate on this issue in the Islamic financial services industry. DOI: 10. 15408 /aiq. v 10 i 1. 612...|$|R
